episodes.title: Bart of Darkness
episodes.plot: Confined to his room with a broken leg, Bart suspects Ned Flanders of murdering Maude; the family's new swimming pool earns Lisa popularity among the neighborhood kids.

episodes.title: Lisa's Rival
episodes.plot: Lisa is jealous when a new girl in class is smarter than she is; Homer obtains a giant mound of sugar.

episodes.title: Another Simpsons Clip Show
episodes.plot: The family recalls past tales of lost love.

episodes.title: Itchy & Scratchy Land
episodes.plot: A family vacation to Itchy & Scratchy Land turns disastrous when the robots malfunction and turn on the tourists.

episodes.title: Sideshow Bob Roberts
episodes.plot: When Sideshow Bob is released from prison and is elected Mayor of Springfield, Bart and Lisa suspect foul play and are determined to expose his corruption.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror V
episodes.plot: The family's job at Mr. Burns' country estate goes awry when Homer goes mad; Homer's attempt to repair a toaster results in inadvertent time travel; The school staff turn cannibalistic.

episodes.title: Bart's Girlfriend
episodes.plot: Bart falls for Reverend Lovejoy's daughter and is surprised when she becomes a bad influence on him.

episodes.title: Lisa on Ice
episodes.plot: Sibling rivalry between Bart and Lisa ensues when they become the star players of their respective ice hockey teams.

episodes.title: Homer Badman
episodes.plot: Homer accidentally lands himself in trouble with the law and with the kids' babysitter after stealing a gummy replica at a candy convention.

episodes.title: Grampa vs. Sexual Inadequacy
episodes.plot: Homer and Abe hit the road to sell Abe's miraculous aphrodisiac.

episodes.title: Fear of Flying
episodes.plot: Marge goes into therapy to cure her of her traumatizing fear of flying.

episodes.title: Homer the Great
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a member of a mysterious organization called the Stonecutters and is heralded as "the chosen one".

episodes.title: And Maggie Makes Three
episodes.plot: Homer recounts the story of Maggie's birth when the kids ask why there are no photos of her in the family album.

episodes.title: Bart's Comet
episodes.plot: Bart discovers a comet that is on a collision course with Springfield.

episodes.title: Homie the Clown
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a Krusty the Clown stand-in, but is mistaken for the real Krusty by the Springfield mafia.

episodes.title: Bart vs. Australia
episodes.plot: In order to prove that toilets flush the opposite direction in Australia, Bart makes a prank call that ends up costing the recipient $900, Bart must apologize.

episodes.title: Homer vs. Patty and Selma
episodes.plot: Desperate for money, Homer takes a loan from Patty and Selma; Bart discovers a natural talent for ballet.

episodes.title: A Star Is Burns
episodes.plot: The citizens of Springfield host their own film festival, with popular movie critic Jay Sherman arriving from New York to judge.

episodes.title: Lisa's Wedding
episodes.plot: A fortune teller gives Lisa a look at her wedding in the year 2010.

episodes.title: Two Dozen and One Greyhounds
episodes.plot: Santa's Little Helper's new mate has puppies, and Mr. Burns schemes to steal them and make them into a coat.

episodes.title: The PTA Disbands
episodes.plot: Bart manipulates Mrs. Krabappel into leading a teachers' strike against Principal Skinner, but is perturbed when Marge becomes his substitute.

episodes.title: 'Round Springfield
episodes.plot: When Bart is hospitalized, Lisa runs into her mentor Bleeding Gums Murphy, who is also a patient, and becomes devastated when he dies soon after.

episodes.title: The Springfield Connection
episodes.plot: Marge deals with corruption and crime when she joins the Springfield police force.

episodes.title: Lemon of Troy
episodes.plot: When a group of Shelbyville kids steal Springfield's sacred lemon tree, Bart and his friends venture there to get the tree back.

episodes.title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part One
episodes.plot: After Mr. Burns steals oil from Springfield Elementary and blocks out the sun, an unknown person shoots him.
